WEBVTT

00:00.860 --> 00:03.761
- Previously on Being Human...

00:03.800 --> 00:05.928
- Hey, it's me.
I need your help.

00:05.970 --> 00:07.768
- You're a vampire?

00:07.800 --> 00:09.939
- You had no right
to turn her!

00:09.970 --> 00:12.109
- We wanted to see
what was so special.

00:12.140 --> 00:13.608
- I feel like a goddess.

00:13.640 --> 00:16.245
- Once the high wears off, it is more
gruesome than you could realize.

00:16.280 --> 00:18.078
- Ahh!

00:18.110 --> 00:20.272
- I'm lonely.
- Me too.

00:20.320 --> 00:22.948
- You can move
with your thoughts.

00:22.990 --> 00:25.516
- Shut up!
- Where are we?

00:25.550 --> 00:26.620
- Danny's old place.

00:26.660 --> 00:28.754
- Danny?
- My fiance.

00:28.790 --> 00:30.758
Danny...

00:30.790 --> 00:32.952
Bridget?

00:37.670 --> 00:39.593
(Insects buzzing, chirping)

00:41.100 --> 00:44.661
- (Aidan): Quick. What's the world's
most rapidly evaporating resource?

00:44.710 --> 00:46.269
- Ahh!
- Oil?

00:46.310 --> 00:48.438
- What is that? Something in the bushes.
- Water.

00:48.480 --> 00:50.244
Fresh air?

00:52.980 --> 00:54.778
Not even close.

00:56.420 --> 00:57.945
** It's gone *

00:57.990 --> 01:00.960
* But I don't even know *

01:02.890 --> 01:05.120
* Like a steam drill... *

01:05.160 --> 01:07.527
When's the last time
you were truly alone?

01:07.560 --> 01:09.699
- Remember the guy
who took your picture?

01:09.730 --> 01:10.822
- Yeah.

01:10.870 --> 01:13.237
- When you didn't
think to yourself...

01:13.270 --> 01:14.863
- Classic.
- Yeah.

01:14.900 --> 01:16.459
- Classic shot.

01:16.510 --> 01:18.831
- "Somebody's watching me?"

01:18.870 --> 01:19.940
(Screaming)

01:19.980 --> 01:22.005
A man can wander for
an eternity these days

01:22.040 --> 01:26.443
before finding a place where
he can be himself, let go...

01:26.480 --> 01:28.710
- We don't want any trouble.
- Sorry.

01:28.750 --> 01:30.411
- ...howl at the moon.

01:30.450 --> 01:33.488
How did we let this
happen to us?

01:33.520 --> 01:37.457
* Was living for the heart... *

01:39.160 --> 01:40.321
- Um... see ya.

01:40.360 --> 01:42.795
- Yeah, good night.
Thank you.

01:44.300 --> 01:47.235
* Ain't love just like
fumbling in the dark? *

01:47.270 --> 01:48.738
(Chuckling)

01:51.540 --> 01:53.702
* She's gone 7 *

01:53.740 --> 01:56.539
* 7 or 8 days *

01:56.580 --> 01:58.844
* She's gone where
I don't even know *

01:58.880 --> 02:00.712
- Why do we insist on looking

02:00.750 --> 02:02.980
when our every impulse
tells us...

02:03.020 --> 02:05.216
* She's gone 7... *

02:05.250 --> 02:06.649
"Look away?"

02:06.690 --> 02:08.886
- Ahh!

02:08.919 --> 02:12.891
* She's gone where
I don't even know *

02:14.460 --> 02:17.862
- Maybe it's because we all
have something to hide.

02:17.900 --> 02:20.562
* Dust the cage... *

02:23.770 --> 02:27.274
That thing
we bury down deep...

02:30.110 --> 02:32.977
* Dog's under the porch light *

02:33.020 --> 02:35.739
* Sleeping with
his one eye open *

02:35.780 --> 02:37.179
* Open for... **

02:37.220 --> 02:40.952
beat back into the darkness
with everything we have.

02:42.330 --> 02:44.219
(Exhales)

02:46.930 --> 02:48.955
We're secretly hoping to see

02:49.000 --> 02:52.766
that the monster inside
each of us is inside us all.

02:52.800 --> 02:54.199
(Screaming)

02:54.240 --> 02:56.095
There it is.

02:56.140 --> 02:58.837
Look hard enough,
you'll see it.

02:58.870 --> 03:01.134
You will be seen.

03:01.180 --> 03:02.739
(Roaring)

03:06.920 --> 03:08.319
(Grunting)

03:08.350 --> 03:10.079
(Birds chirping)

03:11.390 --> 03:12.880
(Exhaling)

03:12.920 --> 03:14.410
- Ah!

03:15.820 --> 03:17.458
- It's OK.

03:18.490 --> 03:21.425
It's just some clothes.
Go ahead.

03:21.460 --> 03:23.269
- It was over
a mile north of here.

03:23.300 --> 03:24.495
- Who are you?

03:24.530 --> 03:26.191
- Seriously, chief,
just get dressed.

03:26.240 --> 03:28.993
You're not the only one
who's uncomfortable.

03:31.970 --> 03:34.837
You know, you suck
at being a werewolf.

03:36.780 --> 03:38.646
It's almost offensive.

03:39.980 --> 03:41.914
- What are you talking about?

03:41.950 --> 03:43.247
- I told you.

03:43.290 --> 03:44.746
It's OK.

03:46.690 --> 03:48.351
Name's Ray.

03:49.430 --> 03:51.922
I'm a werewolf, too.

04:05.040 --> 04:07.475
Come on, man.
Don't be like that.

04:07.510 --> 04:08.807
You took my clothes.

04:08.840 --> 04:10.672
Least you could do
is talk to me!

04:10.710 --> 04:12.678
- Sorry, I don't talk to
delusional people.

04:12.720 --> 04:14.142
- You know
I'm telling the truth.

04:14.180 --> 04:16.547
It's only been a coupe of hours
since your last change.

04:16.589 --> 04:18.046
Your senses
are still blazing.

04:18.089 --> 04:20.478
You could smell
what I am.

04:20.519 --> 04:23.182
Oh, for crying out loud, Josh!

04:33.440 --> 04:35.260
- How do you know my name?

04:35.300 --> 04:38.565
- I been at this
a while, you know?

04:39.840 --> 04:40.978
I can help you.

04:43.780 --> 04:44.941
- How?

04:44.980 --> 04:47.278
Once a month,
I'm an animal,

04:47.320 --> 04:48.879
a killer.

04:48.920 --> 04:52.788
I have to run away from
my home, my friends, everyone.

04:52.820 --> 04:56.188
I have to protect
the world from myself!

04:56.220 --> 04:57.756
- And I can help you
with that.

04:57.790 --> 05:01.954
We could look out for each
other. We keep everyone safe.

05:02.000 --> 05:03.161
What do you say?

05:04.730 --> 05:06.494
- Thanks for the clothes.

05:08.140 --> 05:10.199
- Oh, come on! Josh!

05:21.080 --> 05:23.219
- We're late.
Shower up.

05:26.990 --> 05:29.755
Why are you dressed
like a douche?

05:33.100 --> 05:36.024
- Because a douche
gave me these clothes.

05:36.060 --> 05:39.769
No, sorry, a werewolf douche
gave me these clothes.

05:39.800 --> 05:41.939
- Seriously?
- Oh, I'm dead serious.

05:41.970 --> 05:44.803
Yeah, Ray the werewolf.
He's been watching me.

05:44.840 --> 05:46.035
- No.

05:46.070 --> 05:47.572
- Yes!

05:47.610 --> 05:50.307
(Microwave beeping)

05:50.350 --> 05:53.012
Just when I start to think
that there's hope,

05:53.050 --> 05:55.917
like, real hope for me to be
just like everybody else,

05:55.950 --> 05:58.317
I wake up
and I'm in hell!

05:58.350 --> 06:01.251
- I'm in hell! 1 died
and now I'm actually in hell!

06:01.290 --> 06:02.451
- What happened to you?

06:02.490 --> 06:03.628
- We were just talking
about how I'm in hell,

06:03.660 --> 06:06.288
but whatever,
let's talk about you.

06:06.330 --> 06:07.923
- I just spent my night
watching Danny and Bridget

06:07.960 --> 06:09.519
simper and swoon
over each other.

06:09.570 --> 06:11.993
If I had bodily fluids,
I'd spew them.

06:12.030 --> 06:13.691
- Who is Bridget?

06:13.740 --> 06:15.390
- My best friend
since 3rd grade

06:15.440 --> 06:17.602
- who I now realize
is also a brutal whore.

06:17.640 --> 06:20.632
- You can come and go
as you please now.

06:20.680 --> 06:22.944
- Yeah. Why didn't you just leave?
- That's just it.

06:22.980 --> 06:26.006
I didn't have control. Apparently,
I go wherever my mind goes.

06:26.050 --> 06:28.439
I didn't wanna watch
Danny and Bridget, so I left.

06:28.480 --> 06:31.040
But then I couldn't stop
thinking about them together.

06:31.090 --> 06:32.239
Next thing I know, wham!

06:32.290 --> 06:33.655
- You're watching them.

06:33.690 --> 06:35.556
- It's a vicious cycle!

06:36.890 --> 06:37.857
(Sighs)

06:37.890 --> 06:39.892
Why are you dressed
like a douche?

06:39.930 --> 06:41.819
- Josh met another werewolf.

06:41.860 --> 06:44.898
- Aw!
- Who's stalking him.

06:44.930 --> 06:46.329
- Ew.

06:47.770 --> 06:49.260
- I'm gonna shower.

06:51.270 --> 06:52.578
- What do I do?

06:54.840 --> 06:57.047
- Well, T'll tell you
what you do.

06:57.080 --> 06:59.947
You be strong
and you focus on other things.

06:59.980 --> 07:04.190
- Maybe I'll have your willpower
after being around for a century or two.

07:14.300 --> 07:16.860
(Siren wailing)

07:16.900 --> 07:20.291
- (Man on PA):
Blood drop 3427.

07:20.340 --> 07:23.230
Blood, 3427.

07:23.270 --> 07:24.704
- Hold up!
What are you doing?

07:24.740 --> 07:26.606
- I'm transferring Mr. Shaw.

07:26.640 --> 07:29.075
- Really? Where?
There aren't any beds here.

07:29.110 --> 07:32.671
- You sure? I was sent by
Dr. Prindaar. Maybe you could check.

07:32.720 --> 07:33.676
- Robyn?

07:33.720 --> 07:36.246
Can you get this gentleman's
paperwork started?

07:36.280 --> 07:38.783
We'll get you
all squared away, Mr. Shaw.

07:38.820 --> 07:41.585
You think I don't know how many
beds I have available?

07:41.620 --> 07:44.749
- No, no, it's just that
Dr. Prindaar said--

07:44.790 --> 07:48.420
- Dr. Prindaar is what's clinically
known as a jackass and a coward.

07:48.460 --> 07:50.098
I already informed
Dr. Prindaar

07:50.130 --> 07:52.121
that I don't have
any space for Mr. Shaw.

07:52.170 --> 07:53.899
That's why he had
a dopey, doe-eyed,

07:53.940 --> 07:56.363
sad-looking orderly
bring him down here.

07:56.400 --> 07:58.004
He thought I'd have mercy
"cause you're doe--

07:58.040 --> 08:00.338
- And sad-looking.
I get it.

08:02.240 --> 08:03.275
- Go.

08:06.150 --> 08:07.549
(Clearing throat)

08:07.580 --> 08:09.218
- I don't know, man,

08:09.250 --> 08:11.947
but it's one of
the drawbacks of...

08:11.990 --> 08:13.719
Hey, there he is!

08:13.760 --> 08:17.185
- What are you doing here?
- You ready to talk, chief?

08:17.230 --> 08:19.324
- It's Ray.
- Yeah, thanks. You have to leave.

08:19.360 --> 08:21.397
- All I'm asking for
is one cup of coffee.

08:21.430 --> 08:23.762
- Know what?
- Can we have a minute?

08:25.170 --> 08:27.662
- He knows where I work?
That we're roommates?

08:27.700 --> 08:29.190
- Can I just say something?

08:29.240 --> 08:31.436
- You want me to hang out
with this lunatic? Seriously?

08:31.470 --> 08:33.198
- Josh, you are a rare breed,

08:33.240 --> 08:34.400
but don't you think
it might be good

08:34.440 --> 08:37.000
to spend a little time
with someone like you?

08:38.679 --> 08:40.409
- No. Not really.

08:40.450 --> 08:41.940
The one thing
I've been able to do

08:41.980 --> 08:43.345
with this thing
I carry around with me

08:43.390 --> 08:44.448
is keep it small.

08:44.490 --> 08:46.811
OK? I deserve to contain
my own private hell.

08:46.860 --> 08:48.715
And now this guy pops up,

08:48.760 --> 08:50.751
and suddenly
there's two of us.

08:50.790 --> 08:53.225
If I let him in, Aidan,

08:53.260 --> 08:56.195
it all gets bigger.

08:56.230 --> 08:57.527
- You may only change
once a month,

08:57.570 --> 09:01.461
but your anxiety about who you
are, what you are, it consumes you.

09:01.500 --> 09:03.502
It is not small.

09:09.210 --> 09:12.578
- (Man on PA):
Dr. Smith, please call 7428.

09:15.350 --> 09:17.387
- One cup of coffee.

09:18.390 --> 09:19.812
Tomorrow.

09:19.860 --> 09:21.214
- Sweet!

09:21.260 --> 09:22.921
That's awesome, bro!

09:25.490 --> 09:27.197
- We're not bros.

09:38.510 --> 09:40.000
- You rough with
all the girls,

09:40.040 --> 09:41.474
or is it just
a thing with me?

09:41.510 --> 09:43.569
- What do you want, Rebecca?
- Just to talk.

09:43.610 --> 09:47.410
I know you hate me, but you're
the only one who understands.

09:47.450 --> 09:48.520
- What?

09:48.550 --> 09:50.348
- Just try to remember
for a second

09:50.390 --> 09:51.880
that you give
a damn about me.

09:51.920 --> 09:54.059
I need you to get me out.

09:54.090 --> 09:55.319
Or just...

09:56.320 --> 09:59.153
God, just end this now!

10:03.200 --> 10:05.498
- You wanna get away from
Bishop just like that.

10:05.530 --> 10:06.998
- Bishop is just the tip

10:07.040 --> 10:10.032
of the whole nasty pile
of blood-lusting garbage.

10:10.070 --> 10:11.834
- 'Cause the last I remember,

10:11.870 --> 10:14.100
you were having
the time of your life

10:14.140 --> 10:16.029
tearing through
innocent people.

10:17.280 --> 10:19.248
- I thought
it made me strong,

10:19.280 --> 10:20.975
invincible.

10:22.020 --> 10:25.342
I'm the weakest
thing on earth.

10:25.390 --> 10:29.759
But the rush, the fantasy of how
I'd kill, when I'd Kkill, it's gone.

10:29.790 --> 10:31.656
It's like I snapped out
of twilight sleep,

10:31.690 --> 10:33.692
and now I can hear
people whimper,

10:33.730 --> 10:35.391
see the fear
in their eyes.

10:36.400 --> 10:39.199
I hate what I am...

10:39.230 --> 10:41.062
what I've become.

10:41.100 --> 10:44.229
I can't stop.
I can't fight it.

10:44.270 --> 10:48.605
Not by myself.
- It's... It's not your fault.

10:48.640 --> 10:50.074
You didn't choose.

10:50.110 --> 10:52.101
- No, I didn't.

10:53.820 --> 10:58.041
But everything I've done
since turning...

11:00.090 --> 11:04.482
I could stop. You stopped.
- It's not that easy.

11:04.530 --> 11:05.929
- But you could help me.

11:07.030 --> 11:08.156
- I don't know.

11:09.200 --> 11:11.623
- You wanted to help me.

11:14.000 --> 11:18.062
Doesn't "better late than never"”
count for anything anymore?

11:27.420 --> 11:29.309
- What time does
the game start?

11:29.350 --> 11:30.579
- 7:30.

11:30.620 --> 11:32.987
- We should be done
just in time.

11:33.020 --> 11:34.055
- Ugh, vomit!

11:34.090 --> 11:36.730
- Do you have a strainer?
- Yup.

11:36.760 --> 11:39.081
- (Both):
Bottom-right cabinet.

11:39.130 --> 11:41.326
- You know, we could've
ordered in some pizza.

11:41.360 --> 11:42.452
You didn't
have to cook.

11:42.500 --> 11:43.899
- I love cooking.

11:43.930 --> 11:45.523
- Ha! Please!

11:45.570 --> 11:47.789
- I never knew
you were a baseball fan.

11:47.840 --> 11:50.036
- That's because she's not.
- Oh yeah!

11:50.070 --> 11:52.038
- And you like to cook.

11:52.070 --> 11:53.606
- No, she really can't.

11:53.640 --> 11:55.734
- You should taste it
before you judge.

11:55.780 --> 11:58.249
- "Oh, Danny,
I love baseball and cooking

11:58.280 --> 11:59.975
"and being a slut and lying.

12:00.020 --> 12:01.442
"Will you please do me?"

12:01.480 --> 12:03.346
- Look, what is this?

12:04.950 --> 12:06.611
What are we doing here?

12:06.650 --> 12:08.379
- It's dinner and baseball.

12:08.420 --> 12:09.956
- Yeah, I don't care
about dinner

12:09.990 --> 12:11.879
and I don't care
about the Red Sox game.

12:11.930 --> 12:13.728
All I keep thinking about

12:13.760 --> 12:16.127
is what happened
the other night.

12:16.160 --> 12:18.720
- I was wondering if we were
gonna act like nothing happened.

12:18.770 --> 12:21.330
- Wanna know what's happening?
I'll tell you...

12:21.370 --> 12:23.907
- But then you came over
and it hit me: Why do that?

12:23.940 --> 12:26.659
- ...and you're about to make
a huge mistake!

12:26.710 --> 12:28.235
- Because of Sally.

12:28.280 --> 12:30.647
- Sally! Yes!
Thank you for caring!

12:30.680 --> 12:32.375
- What about us?

12:32.410 --> 12:34.412
I mean, we're still here.

12:34.450 --> 12:35.611
- And so am I!

12:35.650 --> 12:37.709
(Shattering)

12:37.750 --> 12:38.740
Holy crap!

12:38.790 --> 12:40.087
Did I just?

12:40.120 --> 12:42.054
- Let me...
- I did just do that!

12:42.090 --> 12:43.785
- I don't know
what happened.

12:43.830 --> 12:45.628
- I happened!
- That was weird.

12:45.660 --> 12:48.095
(* Soft rock *)

12:49.630 --> 12:53.464
<i>** I know it isn't right... *</i>

12:53.500 --> 12:55.468
- Stop!
- Wait.

12:57.040 --> 12:58.166
I can't do this.

12:59.710 --> 13:01.974
Don't you ever...

13:02.010 --> 13:05.605
I don't know. Don't you
ever feel like she's watching?

13:05.650 --> 13:08.176
- Well, I don't know
about that.

13:08.220 --> 13:11.349
* Who you gonna
run to now... **

13:11.390 --> 13:13.313
Maybe this is
a bad idea.

13:16.060 --> 13:17.824
- I think I should go.

13:21.160 --> 13:22.867
(Sally exhaling)

13:26.230 --> 13:29.268
- (Josh): "Hey, Josh,
how about a cup of coffee...

13:29.300 --> 13:32.031
"and a 10-mile hike
through the woods?"

13:32.070 --> 13:34.232
"Sounds great, Ray!"

13:34.280 --> 13:36.942
- Couldn't do this
in a coffee shop!

13:36.980 --> 13:38.709
We need to be out here.

13:38.750 --> 13:40.878
- For what?
- Your education.

13:40.920 --> 13:46.780
You're a dangerous man, to yourself and to others.
- Think I don't know that?

13:46.820 --> 13:51.428
- So we're gonna teach you
to transform safely.

13:51.460 --> 13:54.225
Rule number one:
No one gets hurt.

13:54.260 --> 13:55.523
All right?

13:55.560 --> 13:57.494
We don't wanna kill anyone

13:57.530 --> 13:59.498
or turn them.

13:59.530 --> 14:01.396
Am I right?

14:04.140 --> 14:06.108
- So, what's rule number 27?

14:06.140 --> 14:09.940
- Well, normally,
you steer clear of vampires,

14:09.980 --> 14:13.917
but you've already
crapped the bed on that one.

14:15.350 --> 14:17.114
What's the deal there, anyway?

14:17.150 --> 14:19.187
Anytime I've ever
been around vamps,

14:19.220 --> 14:21.552
they're breaking
their foot off in my ass.

14:21.590 --> 14:24.287
- No, Aidan's not like that.
He's one of the good ones.

14:24.330 --> 14:26.128
- Oh sure, he must
be part of that

14:26.160 --> 14:30.063
soft-and-cuddly sect of vampires
I've been hearing about.

14:30.100 --> 14:32.626
- Hey, how'd you
find me, anyway?

14:32.670 --> 14:35.230
- Same way I find any of us:

14:36.100 --> 14:38.330
papers, websites.

14:38.370 --> 14:40.099
I look for patterns.

14:40.140 --> 14:43.508
Gloucester has some
strange animal deaths.

14:43.550 --> 14:47.839
You tore up a lot of deer
in these woods, my friend.

14:50.450 --> 14:53.750
- Have you, um...
Are there others?

14:56.260 --> 14:57.853
- Not in these woods.

15:01.200 --> 15:02.929
This is it!

15:02.970 --> 15:04.460
- This is what?

15:05.300 --> 15:07.291
- School.

15:09.100 --> 15:11.205
- You change into
a werewolf in here?

15:11.240 --> 15:12.332
- Nah.

15:12.370 --> 15:14.532
Somebody stumbles
across this place,

15:14.580 --> 15:16.002
you'll both be screwed.

15:17.050 --> 15:18.575
Nah, this place,

15:18.610 --> 15:21.841
it's just somewhere to
keep your stuff dry and safe.

15:21.880 --> 15:23.848
Now...

15:23.890 --> 15:28.054
the key to an easy-and-simple
werewolf transformation

15:28.090 --> 15:29.683
is preparation.

15:29.720 --> 15:33.258
First thing to pack
is a change of clothes,

15:33.300 --> 15:34.927
naturally!

15:34.960 --> 15:38.624
Next up we have wet wipes
to clean yourself off.

15:38.670 --> 15:42.459
I prefer fresh scent.
You look like a citrus guy.

