32:43.090 --> 32:44.683
- Danny?

32:45.330 --> 32:46.820
(Sighing)

32:46.860 --> 32:48.851
- Why did it have
to be Bridget?

32:51.600 --> 32:53.022
(Inhaling)

32:53.070 --> 32:56.495
- You love Danny, right?

32:56.540 --> 32:58.304
And Briget?

32:58.340 --> 33:02.208
- When she's not rubbing her
bits all over my fiance,

33:02.240 --> 33:04.004
yeah, she's the best.

33:04.050 --> 33:07.771
- So what could be better
than 2 people that you love

33:07.810 --> 33:10.472
coming together over the love
that they share for you?

33:10.520 --> 33:13.888
- They're not sharing
the love, Mr. Hallmark.

33:13.920 --> 33:15.854
They're dancing
on my grave.

33:15.890 --> 33:17.415
- Sally.

33:18.360 --> 33:23.594
(Sighing) This life
gets bitterly cold.

33:23.630 --> 33:26.122
Sometimes you just
need to cling to the person

33:26.170 --> 33:28.935
that you can claw your way
out of the dark with.

33:28.970 --> 33:34.534
Danny and Bridget,
they may not be kismet,

33:34.580 --> 33:37.572
but we all deserve
a shot at a normal life.

33:37.610 --> 33:39.442
They do, you do.

33:39.480 --> 33:41.448
- You do.

33:42.480 --> 33:43.948
(Sighing)

33:43.980 --> 33:45.584
- Maybe.

33:50.490 --> 33:52.481
(* Humming *)

33:54.530 --> 33:56.794
- (Sally, echoing):
Bridget, it's OK.

33:56.830 --> 33:57.956
(* Stops humming *)

33:59.230 --> 34:00.561
(* Humming *)

34:00.600 --> 34:03.570
Bridget, I know you
probably can't hear me, but...

34:05.940 --> 34:07.999
I don't know
what else to do.

34:09.179 --> 34:11.274
I need you to know
that it's OK.

34:12.750 --> 34:14.149
I get it.

34:14.179 --> 34:17.571
Please, go to him.

34:17.620 --> 34:20.920
- Hello?
Is someone there?

34:32.100 --> 34:34.239
- This place is really nice.

34:35.739 --> 34:37.060
- Yeah.

34:37.100 --> 34:38.659
And it's been
around forever.

34:38.710 --> 34:41.600
Uh, I think
they redecorated.

34:44.949 --> 34:46.577
- The food looks good.

34:47.449 --> 34:51.512
Really colourful.

34:52.520 --> 34:54.351
(Chuckling)

34:54.389 --> 34:55.289
(Inhaling)

34:55.320 --> 34:56.810
(Cutlery clattering)

34:58.360 --> 35:00.089
Aiden.

35:00.130 --> 35:02.019
- Just, uh, just try.

35:03.030 --> 35:04.919
(Both sighing)

35:13.240 --> 35:15.277
(Rumbling)

35:22.020 --> 35:23.579
(Heart beating)

35:24.920 --> 35:26.115
(Crunching)

35:31.730 --> 35:35.291
- Uh, so, how was
your day anyway?

35:35.330 --> 35:37.594
** All alone in the city *

35:37.630 --> 35:39.291
(Both panting)

35:39.330 --> 35:41.367
* It's like I found my mind *

35:41.400 --> 35:43.459
(Siren in distance)

35:43.500 --> 35:45.309
* Broken bottles *

35:45.340 --> 35:47.707
* And broken bones *

35:47.740 --> 35:50.573
* Keep dreaming
on the edge of the night *

35:50.610 --> 35:51.941
(Both moaning)

35:51.980 --> 35:53.948
<i>* I don't wanna go *</i>

35:53.980 --> 35:57.575
<i>* I don't wanna go back to
the city... ** - School is over.</i>

35:57.620 --> 36:01.409
You have absorbed every morsel
of knowledge I have to offer.

36:01.460 --> 36:02.882
(Both chuckling)

36:02.920 --> 36:04.820
- Thanks, Ray.
I mean that.

36:04.860 --> 36:07.625
- What do you say
we celebrate, eh?

36:07.660 --> 36:09.458
- Yeah, all right.

36:10.230 --> 36:11.664
Where are we?

36:11.700 --> 36:13.259
- Shhh!

36:14.240 --> 36:16.060
See that place?

36:17.070 --> 36:19.368
They gorge
themselves in there.

36:19.410 --> 36:20.468
- Who?

36:20.510 --> 36:21.909
- Who do you think?

36:21.940 --> 36:26.776
They get so stuffed with blood,
they actually get stoned.

36:26.810 --> 36:28.141
Filthy pigs.

36:28.180 --> 36:30.478
- Vampires? There are
vampires in there?

36:30.520 --> 36:32.784
- Yeah. See, this is
the kind of stuff

36:32.820 --> 36:36.654
your boy, Aiden, is not gonna be telling you about.
- Come on!

36:36.690 --> 36:39.489
- That's why I want you
to know everything

36:39.530 --> 36:41.828
that these leeches
are capable of!

36:41.860 --> 36:43.419
Quit running!

36:43.460 --> 36:45.929
- I really don't think
we should be here.

36:45.970 --> 36:49.964
- This is absolutely where we
need to be tonight while we're strong!

36:51.910 --> 36:54.004
I'm proud of you, boy.

36:54.040 --> 36:58.034
You're gonna follow my
lead, and enjoy the party.

37:01.650 --> 37:04.585
Ready to pop
some ticks?

37:04.620 --> 37:06.145
(Chuckling)

37:06.190 --> 37:07.146
<i>Excuse me!</i>

37:07.190 --> 37:08.453
- Wait!

37:08.490 --> 37:10.709
- Excuse me, sir.

37:10.760 --> 37:13.058
- No, thanks. I'm full.

37:13.090 --> 37:14.455
(Groaning)

37:14.500 --> 37:15.649
- Ray!

37:15.700 --> 37:17.623
(Grunting)

37:17.660 --> 37:20.061
(Ray laughing)

37:21.770 --> 37:22.737
(Laughing)

37:22.770 --> 37:26.400
(Thudding and Ray grunting)

37:30.140 --> 37:31.904
Ray, he's--

37:31.950 --> 37:34.100
- What? He's dead!

37:34.150 --> 37:36.073
He died a long time ago.

37:36.120 --> 37:38.214
How can you just stand there?

37:38.250 --> 37:39.945
Don't you want some payback?

37:39.990 --> 37:43.210
A little retribution for
all the crap we had to take

37:43.260 --> 37:45.228
from pieces of
garbage like this?

37:45.260 --> 37:48.855
Day in, day out.

37:48.900 --> 37:51.460
(Ray shouting, indistinct)

37:51.500 --> 37:54.367
- Well, look at this.

37:55.370 --> 37:58.135
A couple of strays.

37:58.170 --> 37:59.365
- You want a piece of this?

37:59.410 --> 38:01.003
- Ray, let's go!

38:01.040 --> 38:03.407
- I think I have
a little room left.

38:03.440 --> 38:05.704
- Oh!

38:05.750 --> 38:08.447
- Well, that just
leaves you and I'm--

38:17.190 --> 38:19.830
- Ray, we need to get
the hell out of here now!

38:19.860 --> 38:22.352
- Hey, you're not
the only one that bites!

38:22.400 --> 38:23.993
(Growling)

38:25.800 --> 38:28.462
(All grunting)

38:34.480 --> 38:35.834
(Teeth clicking)

38:35.880 --> 38:39.305
- Wait!
Get out of here now!

38:39.350 --> 38:40.977
- He's mine!

38:41.010 --> 38:42.876
- We gotta go!
Come on!

38:44.520 --> 38:45.919
- That's it, Josh!

38:45.950 --> 38:47.918
Tear him apart!

38:47.950 --> 38:50.453
(Growling)

38:54.800 --> 38:56.996
- Hey.
- Hi.

38:57.560 --> 38:59.028
(Moans)

38:59.800 --> 39:01.393
It's OK.

39:01.440 --> 39:04.364
- All right. Well, what's OK?
- This. Us.

39:04.410 --> 39:05.502
We don't have
to feel guilty.

39:05.540 --> 39:07.099
I think Sally
tried to tell me.

39:07.140 --> 39:09.404
- Tell you? What-- -
I... I guess. I don't know.

39:09.440 --> 39:11.772
I felt something.
A feeling of peace.

39:11.810 --> 39:13.539
- Wait, wait. What?

39:14.720 --> 39:16.370
- I think it was her.

39:18.020 --> 39:19.283
(Sighing)

39:27.190 --> 39:29.090
- I can't do this anymore.

39:29.130 --> 39:30.222
- Hey, sweetheart.

39:30.260 --> 39:31.227
- I can't.

39:31.260 --> 39:32.466
- It's OK, it's OK.

39:32.500 --> 39:34.127
I brought you some.

39:35.540 --> 39:38.237
I am not a monster,
neither are you.

39:38.270 --> 39:39.704
- But we are!

39:41.140 --> 39:43.370
<i>We are!</i>

39:55.960 --> 39:57.655
(Tap running)

39:59.990 --> 40:03.324
Everyday is gonna make us
want to rip our fingernails out

40:03.360 --> 40:05.897
if we have to keep
living like this.

40:07.770 --> 40:10.637
I can't go to a restaurant
and pretend to be human,

40:10.670 --> 40:14.334
when all I want to do
is eat the table next to me.

40:14.370 --> 40:15.769
(Sniffling)

40:15.810 --> 40:17.938
I'm not that strong.

40:17.980 --> 40:19.573
(Tap stops running)

40:19.610 --> 40:22.045
- I will be strong
for both of us.

40:24.380 --> 40:26.189
I've been here before.

40:28.050 --> 40:31.623
When you wake up in the morning,
you will feel better.

40:41.900 --> 40:43.538
- Hey, guys!

40:43.570 --> 40:45.368
It's Danny!

40:53.510 --> 40:55.114
Sally?

40:59.220 --> 41:00.312
(Danny sighing)

41:00.350 --> 41:02.455
** Everyone's raining *
Are you here?

41:02.490 --> 41:05.482
* Everyone's pouring *

41:05.530 --> 41:07.988
(Chuckling)

41:11.330 --> 41:15.563
* Everyone's hailing
Everyone's storming * Sally, I--

41:20.640 --> 41:22.972
* Everyone's raging *

41:23.010 --> 41:25.445
* Everyone's r oaring *
Are you here?

41:30.720 --> 41:33.485
* Everyone's raining *

41:33.520 --> 41:36.160
* Everyone's pouring *

41:38.960 --> 41:41.349
* My love **

41:42.360 --> 41:44.761
(Car honking in distance)

41:46.800 --> 41:50.464
- You should've seen the look
on his face when I bit him.

41:50.500 --> 41:52.468
I mean, you know,
there's surprise

41:52.510 --> 41:56.401
and there there's this-guy- almost-bit
my-cheek-off kind of surprise.

41:56.440 --> 41:57.532
(Chuckling)

41:57.580 --> 41:59.400
- I can't believe
I just did that.

41:59.450 --> 42:01.009
- You need a beer, my friend.

42:02.850 --> 42:06.741
- S-s-seriously,
I don't do things like that.

42:06.790 --> 42:09.589
I don't-- I don't
beat men in alleys.

42:09.620 --> 42:11.418
- Those weren't men.

42:16.500 --> 42:18.320
Be honest, though.

42:18.360 --> 42:20.397
Felt good, didn't it?

42:23.940 --> 42:25.863
Hey, look at me.

42:27.510 --> 42:31.071
Hey. H . e onr

42:31.110 --> 42:32.475
- It's all right.

42:33.450 --> 42:35.009
You all right?

42:37.280 --> 42:39.317
I have been
watching you, Josh.

42:40.450 --> 42:41.815
And what I saw tonight...

42:41.860 --> 42:43.180
(Chuckles)

42:43.220 --> 42:48.556
...that look on your face when
you were tearing that leech up...

42:48.600 --> 42:50.921
there was joy
in there.

42:50.960 --> 42:54.999
You enjoyed it
deep, deep down

42:55.040 --> 42:56.690
where the wolf lives.

42:56.740 --> 42:59.903
You know it felt good.

42:59.940 --> 43:01.101
(Sniffling)

43:10.680 --> 43:13.786
** Wolves and
werewolves, baby *

43:13.820 --> 43:16.357
* Scratchin' at your door *

43:20.960 --> 43:23.520
* Said there's wolves
and werewolves, baby *

43:23.560 --> 43:26.097
* Scratchin' at your door *

43:30.370 --> 43:32.566
* I think I fed 'em earlier *

43:32.610 --> 43:35.136
* I don't know what
they're here for... **
